        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 5:03PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 503 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Terlingua, or 13 miles northeast of Lajitas, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chisos Basin, Terlingua, Study Butte, Big Bend National Park,
Terlingua Ranch Airport, and Terlingua Ranch Lodge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
